content: The latest release from Play store stopped working for me on my Pixel 3/Android 11, but I grabbed 5.5.1 beta from Github and it's looking good. Thanks!

Streaming video content is completely broken regardless of what I do and listening to podcasts consistently crash the app. Album art never lines up with the proper podcast. Dead app. Can't even list your music alphabetically and it has several bugs. Find another app.
I paid for this app, and found a problem with the equalizer, so I reported a bug on github with a complete description of the problem. It simply got closed without even a reply. Amazing!

Stability, efficiency, simplicity, and endless working devs make this subsonic client the best in its class. -update Still the absolute best in its class, but PLEASE GIVE ME ENQUEUE BY DEFAULT OPTION! Thank you! 11.16.18 I don't know if I am the only user experiencing a locking app, random fc's, random disconnects. Android 8.0.0 s9+ other than these recent hiccups, the best subsonic client ever! 2020 please fix the s20+ ui. Charge more if you have to but communicate.

As of June 2020 DSub is working beautifully, at home and away. I've experienced none of the UI issues that other people are reporting, and the Android Auto implementation has been flawless so far. I love that I can specify a different URL for my server while I'm at home so that I can stay connected via my local subnet. This is a very thoughtful and feature-rich app that was well worth the price. I'm extremely happy with DSub.

Used to love this app, happily paid for it, certainly got my moneys worth over the years, but moving on due to the glacial pace of updates and the current state of the app not keeping pace with more modern phones. At this point I cannot in good concience reccomend anyone paying for this. You can get the same or better from free android apps that work with all of the modern forks of subsonic that are not of the same unfortunate closed source nature that subsonic went (I always appreciated the open source github for this app). If I get some kind of notification of major updates in the future I will certainly come back, but until then, so long and thanks for the memories.

I've been a DSub user for a while, but it's lack of development has left it full of bugs. On Android 10 for me it becomes unusable very quickly as a media list becomes permanent on the screen, showing the scroll-able version behind. Impossible to see the list like this. Until now this was the best *sonic player.
Visually unappealing. Cast volume not exposed to the phone, which sort of defeats casting. Work in progress looking like abandonware.

Great app, BUT is unable to detect/read the network SSID in the latest Android version(s). Because of this, users can no longer run it locally on their home network without adding that as a second server with its own library, which I prefer not to do. Dev, please fix this!
Was once good, now crazy buggy.
Great app, I've used it for years and it's been solid. Is there any way to add a 'Play Next' context menu? Pretty please.
Very good player for Subsonic server, but has not been updated in quite a while.

Noticed a few long outstanding bugs in this otherwise excellent App (Pro version). 1: I group my audio in Subsonic as Music, Audio, Series, AudioBooks. But when I select in Dsub my Music folder, and then do a randomise, I get some audio from the other groups added! 2: The Equaliser never stays on between sessions or remembers my custom preset. 3: On occasion, it skips a track when I do a next track tap. These seem to be when the current playing song is currently out of sight at the top. I've noticed this in Android 9 and now Android 10 on my Samsung S9.

Had to uninstall this recently because of the massive battery drain (even when not using the app) since upgrading my phone to Android 10. Worked great previously, but it doesn't look like the app is actually being maintained.
Best subsonic streamer

Great app for my Airsonic music server! Lightweight, simple yet powerful and no hiccups in the playback. Easy to set up and configure multiple server connections to fast switch between WiFi and Internet. Turn OFF the "DLNA Enabled" option in the "Casting" menu and there will be zero battery drain issues.
Plays music fine, but drains the battery quite dramatically, even when not in use. Have no choice but to uninstall it.
Haven't used it in months but keeps draining my battery.
Nice app, good for offline and online playback. It's showing track numbers despite being configured not to do so.
By far the best Subsonic app, works well on all my devices. Five years later, I still hate Material Design (thanks Google), but Floss gives great support and the app is still solid.

content: Best app for *Sonic apps, by far.
replyContent: You have to go into system Settings -> Application Manager -> DSub -> Clear Cache/Data.  Something in the update process broke DSub for everybody and this seems to fix it for most people.

replyContent: Can you check that it is still an issue after the latest update?  It appears that the gapless playback isn't working correctly on some galaxy phones, so I added some code to manually check whether the next song was automatically started.

Extremely pleased every time this app is updated. Floss is a developer that listens, and is always open to adding cool new features. Not only the best subsonic client out there, but my favorite music client period on Android. 5 stars well deserved. Edit: Currently experiencing battery drain on Android 10
Excellent Airsonic client. Create a fully functional jukebox at home, available to each member of the family. Great interface, simple and efficient.

For some reason the app won't download music to the phone when I'm connected to WiFi but on mobile data it works fine.

I used this app on an LG V10 for years with no trouble. Now, on my new Note 10+, it quits playing at entirely random times. I thought it might have to do with the widget, but I uninstalled it and the problem persisted. It's not related to the screen going dark or the playing position in the song.
Does not support LDAP login.
Long time user of DSub alongside my Madsonic server instance. It just works with no fuss. Cache sync lets me take my music with me easily wherever and whenever I want. Great app.

So this is supposed to be the heroic indy developer better version of subsonic because this version has offline caching, whoop di doo. This feature is the sole reason I bought it. BUT WHERE THE HELL IS THE MENU OPTION TO ACTUALLY SHOW ALL OFFLINE CACHED CONTENT??? IT'S MISSING! No, I'm not going to scroll through each & every album in the hopes that I MIGHT find the tracks that have been cached offline. Fix this, it's basic. Maybe I'll just refund and use the mod.

Feature and UI-wise, this seems to be the best subsonic player I've tested on Android.  Alas, it's not without problems.  On Android 9 on my car's head unit, DSub will not play any songs that are cached on either the device internal memory or SD card.  If I start a non-cached song, it plays, but then if I got back and play it again, I'll hear 200-400ms of the song then it will try and skip to the next.  DSub skips all songs until it finds one that it can stream (i.e. not cached).  Same for mp3 and FLAC files.  In case something was messing up with my Subsonic server, I did a binary compare of the cached files on the SD cards that DSub created and the original files - they are bit-for-bit identical.   This is a deal breaker for me.  The ability to cache and playback files is what I bought this app for.
Not working on Android 9....won't recognize local network or SSID. Works in all older versions of Android
replyContent: According to the Developer Console: "You've made all purchases of your app available for Family Library".  If it's still not working for you I don't think there is anything I can do on my end.

content: Really love using this hooked up to my Ampache server, but wish you could make it simpler (less steps) to give a 1-5 rating to songs. if you're not on the playlist view you have to go back to it, then select a couple of options. could the 1-5 be visible on the Now Playing screen, above the thumbs up/down, star and comments?
bitdefender is detecting aggressive malware in latest version. never had this problem before. app always works great. Probably false alarm.

The official client is a huge steaming pile of you-know-what. I was almost done with subsonic completely until I found this app. Huge thanks to the dev(s?) for putting the time in on this. edit: A few bugs have cropped up along with frequent crashes and interface freezes (music still playing).
Well, it's a great app!
No Joy with Chromecast.

The app is working great so far.   However, I notice when it caches songs that it displays a pinned icon next to it, I cached some songs, and after its done, and I go back to look at the song the pinned icon is gone, so I am assuming the song is still cached regardless. Simply fantastic!!
not working for me, asked for a refund.

My favortie Android app. Actually one of my primary motivations for switching to Android in the first place. I have been using this app almost daily for the past 3 years and I am convinced that there is no better way to access music on mobile. The functionality blows away any paid streaming service and the app itself obliterates the iOS counterparts. I'd been using the F-Droid version up until upgrading to Android P but I was happy to pay for this version for the simple LAN-SSID fix. THANK YOU!

Still after many years it goes wrong 50% of the time when you press back, with an overlay of the previous screen making it unusable! Love the app but it sucks having to restart it so often. Happens on oneplus, note 9, etc.

It's a great app, but the equalizer settings don't save. So whenever the app is exited and relaunched I need to tune them again. This sounds minor but it's a couple times a day and adds up to a regular annoyance.

The server component is inherently flawed. After a short but predictable time the server database becomes corrupt. Edit: After posting talking about the DATABASE corruption the author questions why I would want it fixed? That's way out of line. In an attempt to resolve this by using an sql database it turns out his product has serious issues with an external database presenting sql errors rather than opening some podcasts. Easily reproducible yet no effort is put in to doing that. Fix it!
replyContent: At this point it is a couple of years of "modifying" it and adding features users have asked for.  I'm not looking for the holy grail here, so I'm not sure why you expect it to be innovative.  DSub doesn't do any magic when connecting. I am not sure why you think it is DSubs fault that there is a connection problem from your work.

I've been a long time DSub supporter, and it's still the best Subsonic client. I'm using it with Airsonic now. Has all the features of a great music player, like gapless playback. Custom cache size lets me customize it to work perfectly over a low quality connection.

replyContent: For the no playing issue: You have to go into system Settings - Application Manager - DSub - Clear Cache/Data.  Something in the update process broke DSub for everybody and this seems to fix it for most people.  For the multiple songs issue you should be able to just upgrade to the latest version of DSub.

perfect

Overall the look and layout feels good and I like the full screen mode. The music caching option for seamless playback works great, esp. with spotty connections I might get with my cell carrier to my servers at home.  An improvement that the app could use is less wasted space towards the middle when the song is playing. Maybe a visualizer could be added or easier access to the equalizer and other audio settings could be made available without clicking around too much.   Would like to see an section or tab for cached songs for easy playback.  Lastly I wished swipping back or forwards on a track would do a slight animation to provide a little more confidence when switching between tracks.   Otherwise, great and app work!
Still AWESOME

I love dsub and use it everyday. the only thing I'd like to see added is a category that has all cached content under it, with the usual options of playing/shuffling/adding to queue. Thanks, amazing app!

This is a great app in almost every respect but it has one major flaw - no gapless playback when casting to my Chromecast Audio. This means that there is a gap of silence between each track during playback which really interrupts the flow when I play an album which has seamless transitions between songs or a comedy album. If this one issue could be fixed this would be a 5 star review but until then it means I don't get as much use out of it as I'd like.

Great app.  Only drawback is the apparent inability to save to external storage even when rooted. The option is there but not selectable. I've got a 64gb SD card yet I'm limited to the small amount of internal storage that is shared with many other apps.

Other than having Chromecast support this app doesn't appear better in any way than free alternatives like Ultrasonic. The UI is clunky and the Chromecast-support has so many bugs. To name a few the volume controls never seem to work while casting and if you stop a song and close the app to cast from another app, this app will try to reconnect to Chromecast and override whatever other app you tried to cast from which is really annoying. Even if you stop the current song and kill the app after casting the next time you start the app it'll automatically try to start Casting again.

content: a few things are annoying. 1) Why even have an online/offline mode, why isn't there just a check if a network link is up? Doesn't Android have that capability? I allways have to remember to switch back to online mode, or the sync won't work and the UI works differently depending on which mode i'm currently in. 2) Why does the creation of a random playlist in offline-mode sometimes take >1 min. when it is instant in online-mode, whether i'm actually online or not?
Works great with new devices but not playing anything on Android 4.4.2...

It seems the latest update does not authenticate correctly with basic auth anymore. I am using an nginx reverse proxy in front of libresonic.   Testing connection in the app gives "Connection failure. Resource not found. Please check the server address." My nginx log shows a 401 for the GET request to /libresonic/rest/ping.view. If I disable basic auth, the test is successful and the app works.  Edit: I was able to get the previous version from the developer's GitHub right away, which still worked, and the developer sent me an updated version very quickly. The update was included in the next Play Store release, and everything is 100% again.  Great developer and amazing app!
replyContent: If you update it should be fixed now

content: Very nice software. But the Subsonic server (not DSub) has a few issues concerning browsing large collections:  You can list 1) albums alphabetically; 2) Genres; or 3) browse the library  as file structure (typically Artist\Album) or tags (Artist\Album).  But, Subsonic has no handling of multiple artists or multiple genres on one album, even creating problems since semicolon ";" is simply omitted in artists, leading to strange artists like "BachMozart" as opposed to "Bach; Mozart", or one entry "Bach" and another "Mozart" for same album. Can be mitigated somewhat by the "Browse by tags" server setting, resulting in  an artist called "Bach/Mozart". Likewise the genre listing suffers when the genre filed has many entries, since each combination of many  genres is understood as one new unique genre, e.g. "Jazz; Bob" is not the same as "Bob; Jazz", nor "Jazz", nor "Bob". Many other databases like MediaMonkey, iTunes handles all this excellently, but not Subsonic. Conclusion is that DSub, though as excellent as it gets, is limited when navigate among your 100.000 albums/tracks. DSub still gets 5 stars. But Subsonic, please do fix this.

I love the features on this player, but there is one bug that annoys the heck out of me. Many times, when I skip to the next track on the playlist, there is no music playing even though the progress bar and time is moving along. It didn't always do this before, so I don't know what happened. I've used this player for well over a year, but this problem just started like a month or two ago. *update*: I did try reinstalling Dsub, but after reinstalling, i found that it remembered all of my settings. I found that the playback problem seems to be related to my bluetooth speaker (UE Boom). When i use dsub w/o the bluetooth speaker, everything seems to behaves normally. Very strange problem. Possibly the player stops sending signals to the speaker in between song skips and it has trouble reinitiating when the next song starts? I can hear slight clicky sounds on the bluetooth speaker when skipping tracks.
replyContent: You can try reinstalling DSub. That will reset the settings and make sure it wasn't a corrupted update screwing stuff up.

A.very good subsonic client - easy to use, good layout, reliable. My only gripe is the lack of support for multiple tags in the same field, i.e. tags separated by some separator, for example "jazz;free jazz;experimental" as the genre tag, which should result in the song being found under all of the three genres listed, or "Sunn O)));Boris" as the artist field, which should result in the song (and the whole album of the song) being listed under both the artists "Sunn O)))" and "Boris". This is the way squeezeserver operates and really should be the standard, but I am yet to find a mobile music streaming app that allows this basic functionality. Edit: Changed the rating to 5 stars after a developer reply explaining that lack of multiple tag/tag separator issue is a limitation of the subsonic server itself and not due to app design.
replyContent: That's not something I can control unfortunately. Support for that has to come from the server. DSub is just displaying the genres and what songs belong to that genre the server serves up.

content: This is a great application.  My only issue would be... Album titles don't scroll. I couldn't find anything in the settings for this.

I am able to stream my videos again.  I noticed some new streaming features were added in settings.  I was able to revert back to a transcoding mode and I can stream my videos again.     FFMPEG revisits the beginning portions of a video stream after it is done with a transcoding, but when downloading via the cache function this is not possible as the file is on the remote end, as a result my downloaded videos are not seekable, which is a drag.  Looking to see if there is any workaround to this.
Best

content: Excellent! Works great with subsonic on mmpc and streams all music. Droid razr Maxx
Works with subsonic and supysonic, sounds better than Spotify, and all my music is in one place and available to all the apps on my phone or to DJ with in USB mode.  The ultimate music player!

No question here, this application vastly improves on what the subsonic app started. The Dev is responsive, so much so that he even included my suggested code for a bug fix when a new version of android came out for my device but not yet for his. :D

Way better than the stock app the new slider feature excellent addition to a already great app keep up the good work I recommend this app for anybody that has subsonic server This is the 2nd time I have been here just have a suggestion a volume control in the player would be really nice   the new update really messed the volume up won't turn up or down it put a phone volume on my tab 2 I have to go into settings to control the media volume and you can't turn the Bluetooth on without it pausing all the time

content: Best Subsonic client on Android, with frequent updates.

replyContent: No problems that I am aware. Try using the send log feature from the main screen after letting it try to download for a second. I can see if it is throwing a error internally.

content: New UI is incredible. This app is absolutely indispensable to me, and continued work from the developer makes it better and better every time.

content: Amazing app, been using it forever!  Frequent updates - even video streaming works almost perfectly (audio is absolutely perfect). Basically cannot use the app+internal device speakers right now.  Headphones (BT+wired) still work great!  EDIT:  Any possible way we can get seeking (of some type - even manual "force to location" would be awesome) for video?  No matter which player/transcoding settings I have tried, I still cannot get seek/FW video while playing.

Could you add a "Default to Remote Control" option under playback like some of the other apps though? I cant be the only one that finds that useful. Great outside of that though!  Edit: Nevermind, I see that the setting persists once you change it the first time.  Awesome app.
Really enjoy this app. Gives great value to my home rig.

Here you have offline starring, it saves your scrobbles and then asks if you want to sync them once you go back online. You can also fine-tune the amount of memory for cached songs. Finally what I most appreciate is the persistent notification with play/pause, next and previous. You also have them on the lock screen which was really missing.  And it's frequently updated! Definitely worth it!

Server is on Windows Vista, I'm using a nexus 4 to stream  I spoke too soon, an uninstall and reinstall of subsonic fixed everything. Port tests all checked out ok, this is a must have app

content: Good but fails to play transcoded files. no idea why. Feel free to contact me if you want help reproing or want me to debug anything.

content: Stable and awesome. Five stars! Woop wooooop!

After the original subsonic app Stabbed already paying customers in the back I started looking for a completely new way To listen to my music. Luckily I stumbled upon this app which allowed me to continue using my same setup and gain many sorely needed features at the same time. Daneren listens to user feedback and is incredibly quick at implementing new features.  This is the most used and most loved app on my phone.

Subsonic is the best media streaming server out there. Sure there is a small fee for a lifetime license on the server to enable mobile streaming but its WELL worth it. This app is by far a better version than the official client. Its definitely worth the few bucks to have all the flexibility.

Great support, consistently updated, and it works ridiculously well.   Subsonic changed the way I look at music and media management, and DSub put me in absolute control of Subsonic.   If you're a naysayer, take five minutes, and go to the forums for support. If you aren't willing to put effort into understanding a service that works on virtually any device in the world, and gives you access to your media, maybe you shouldn't have access to your media... Yet. ;-)   'Nuff said.

Dsub fills the gaps in the stock subsonic app. Just being able to access controls from the notification panel is worth the price of admission, and you get o much more on top of that! Great job. I'm happy to pay for open source software.

Don't be misled by Scott L's long review about being ripped off. He is has no idea what he is talking about. The donation is to use the subsonic server with mobile apps and is a lifetime donation. This app is developed independently by a different developer simply to improve upon the official app.
App works as advertised. (great!)  Developer provides regular updates and improvements.

Very surprised that neither the overview or any of these reviews point out that the $1.99 is for a 30 day trial, after which you must "donate" between 10 & 50 British pounds if you want to continue using the app.   Naturally the site does not inform you what your "donation" entitles you to, but considering the scam perpetuated here, I suspect 10 pounds will get you six months at most. I previously used Audiogalaxy, a free app that worked great but sadly, is no longer supported.  I had hoped DSub would be at least as good (after all it costs money) but sadly found it frequently does not recognize audio files with FLAC or .shn extensions. Overall, DSub would be a disappointing product for $1.99; and an absolute rip off for failing to advise "customers" of the 30 day limitation.  I'm amazed that the Google Play Developer Distribution Agreement allows Floss to list this app on their site without providing full disclosure concerning the limitation of the service.
replyContent: The 30 day trial is a limitation imposed by the Subsonic server software, not by DSub.  I am a different developer then the person who created Subsonic, and cannot dictate what Sindre does and does not do with his server software.

This just keeps getting better and better. Keep up the great work!
Worth the price. No additional add interrupts. Author very responsive to issues.

Great dev, worth buying to support the amount of features this has over the official app like lock screen and pausing audio with navigation etc. Pay upfront for a better app that is not plagued by ads like the official one now is from the play store!

For anyone experiencing 'java.lang.OutOfMemory' errors whilst using this (or any other) app, it's a server issue. The only way I solved this was to completely redeploy Subsonic.
Very good much better than the official client

I bought it for the single reason of hoping it worked with my car's bluetooth playback better than the official Subsonic app.  Google Play and even Apollo will display track information and album artwork on my car's dash monitor when playing songs over a bluetooth connection.  Next/Prev track work great with those two apps.  Unfortunately, none of this works properly with DSub or the official Subsonic app.  When I hit next/prev track it stops playing.  I have to hit play to make it play the next track.  I find the DSub/Subsonic interfaces much more intuitive and easier to use than Google Play Music app so this is extremely disappointing.   I'm basically stuck using dsub/subsonic apps to download music to my phone and using different apps to actually play back the music.    Otherwise this is a great alternative to the stock app.  So if you don't care about bluetooth then I do highly recommend this.  ***EDIT*** Beta is available that makes bluetooth work PERFECTLY in my car.   5 stars for when that beta is released to the play store.  Well done dev!
Top developer who is active on the forums and quick to answer questions. He has already added 2 features that I requested. Well worth the money.
Great app and great support from the dev.

Started using this because the main subsonic app derps pretty hard at bluetooth controls.
